    .support-card {
      width: min(100%, 36rem);
      background: transparent;
    }

    /* One UNIFORM size for all 4 illustrations (user directive 2026-07-09,
       phone screenshots): the previous per-illustration desktop-native
       ceilings (Capital 29.15rem, Expertise 7.83rem — itself an earlier
       user-requested halving, superseded by this — Infrastructure 15.3rem,
       Piloting 27.52rem) made Capital/Piloting fill nearly the whole phone
       viewport while Expertise stayed tiny. All four now render at the same
       compact 10rem (160px, size chosen by the user from offered options),
       so the stacked mobile rhythm reads consistently. */
    .art {
      justify-self: center;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 10rem;
    }
    /* Halved per the same feedback, same card: "02 | WHO YOU WORK WITH" specifically
       (not the other three cards' eyebrows, which the feedback slide never mentions).
       .card-eyebrow's own font-size (above) is one shared rule used by all four cards
       and already resolves to a flat 1.375rem below 1200px (the --support-stage-scale
